               <head>A Persian translation of part of Alf laylah wa-laylah</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85049710">
                  <summary>A Persian translation of the first 200 nights of the <title>Alf laylah
                        wa-laylah</title> (<title xml:lang="ar">الف ليلة وليلة</title>) translated
                     by Murād ʻAlī Muʼaddī(?) of the ẓillah Allahabad. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_598-item1">
                     <author key="person_f7953">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Murād ʻAlī Muʼaddī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">مراد علی مؤدی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22405">Tarjumah-’i Alf Laylā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22405">ترجمهٔ الف ليلة </title>
                     <colophon>(F. 326r) Completed on 17th July 1825 corresponding to 29 Zu’l-Qaʻdah
                        1240 AH by <persName role="scr" key="person_f7954">Ḥimāyat ʻAlī</persName>
                        in the Shalimar garden at the request of Capt. <persName role="pat"
                           key="person_f7955">Stapleton</persName> and General Ochterlony [ie.
                           <persName role="pat" key="viaf_69802904">Major-General Sir David
                           Ochterlony, 1758-182</persName>5]. </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>Followed on f. 327 by notes on reading and writing (در خواندن و نوشتن)
                           and on f. 329 on acting justly (در انصاف کردن). </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
